Usage: modify_ccopt_skew_group [-help] [-make_exclusive] -skew_group <name> [ -add_sinks <pins> | -remove_sinks <pins> ] [ -add_ignore_pins <pins> | -remove_ignore_pins <pins> ]

-help                       # Prints out the command usage
-add_ignore_pins <pins>     # ignore pins to add to the skew group
                            # (string, optional)
-add_sinks <pins>           # sink pins to add to the skew group
                            # (string, optional)
-make_exclusive             # set the exclusive_sinks_rank of the current skew
                            # group to be the highest one (bool, optional)
-remove_ignore_pins <pins>  # ignore pins to remove from the skew group
                            # (string, optional)
-remove_sinks <pins>        # sink pins to remove from the skew group
                            # (string, optional)
-skew_group <name>          # user-defined identifier for the skew group to be
                            # modified (string, required)